            <!-- Slide 1: Introduction -->
            <div id="slide-1" class="slide active">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center space-y-8 md:space-y-0 md:space-x-8">
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
                        <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/2563eb/ffffff?text=Al-Khwarizmi+in+Baghdad" alt="Artistic impression of Al-Khwarizmi in the House of Wisdom, Baghdad." class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full">
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">A Visionary from the Islamic Golden Age</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                            Muhammad ibn Musa al-Khwarizmi ($c. 780 - c. 850$) was a Persian mathematician and astronomer who served as a scholar at the House of Wisdom in Baghdad. His work was pivotal to the development of modern science, particularly in the fields of mathematics and computing.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                            The name "algorithm" is a Latinized version of his last name, "al-Khwarizmi." This alone speaks to his lasting impact, as algorithms are the fundamental building blocks of all modern computing and artificial intelligence.
                        </p>
                        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-3">
                            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kQDjnm8tJi4" target="_blank" class="flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full shadow-md hover:bg-blue-700 transition duration-300">
                                Watch: Al-Khwarizmi: The Father of Algebra
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Slide 2: Major Contributions -->
            <div id="slide-2" class="slide">
                <div class="flex flex-col-reverse md:flex-row items-center space-y-8 md:space-y-0 md:space-x-8">
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Foundational Works in Mathematics</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                            Al-Khwarizmi's most significant work was his book, *Al-Kitāb al-mukhtaṣar fī ḥisāb al-jabr wa’l-muqābala*, which translates to "The Compendious Book on Calculation by Completion and Balancing." This book is considered the birth of algebra. The term "algebra" is derived from the Arabic word "al-jabr" (الجبر) from the title of this work, which means "completion."
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4 space-y-2">
                            <li>He provided systematic solutions for linear and quadratic equations.</li>
                            <li>He introduced the Hindu-Arabic numeral system, including the concept of zero, to the Western world.</li>
                            <li>His methods were described without symbols, using geometric proofs and written descriptions.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-3">
                            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q0I8ffMbkWs" target="_blank" class="flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full shadow-md hover:bg-blue-700 transition duration-300">
                                Watch: Geometric Proofs of Algebra
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
                        <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/2563eb/ffffff?text=Geometric+Algebra" alt="Diagram showing al-Khwarizmi's geometric method for solving quadratic equations." class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Slide 3: Influence on AI -->
            <div id="slide-3" class="slide">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center space-y-8 md:space-y-0 md:space-x-8">
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
                        <img src="https://placehold.co/600x400/2563eb/ffffff?text=Algorithms+and+AI" alt="Illustration of computer code and algorithms." class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full">
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">The Foundation of Computing and AI</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                            Beyond his contributions to algebra, Al-Khwarizmi's work laid the groundwork for modern computer science. The term "algorithm," a Latinization of his name, refers to a step-by-step procedure for solving a problem. This is the very essence of how computers operate.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                            Modern AI, from machine learning to neural networks, relies on complex algorithms to process data, recognize patterns, and make decisions. Al-Khwarizmi's systematic, logical approach to problem-solving, without which these advancements would not be possible, continues to be a cornerstone of this field.
                        </p>
                        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-3">
                            <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/387711108_Muhammad_ibn_Musa_al-Khwarizmi_The_Pioneer_of_Algorithms_and_His_Enduring_Legacy_in_Artificial_Intelligence" target="_blank" class="flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full shadow-md hover:bg-blue-700 transition duration-300">
                                Read: His Legacy in AI
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
